<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Calculates a 64-bit to 128-bit multiply, then XOR folds it.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192" lineLink="#ae07c124bf50a0ad869649d3e1d0def90"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t <a href="#ae07c124bf50a0ad869649d3e1d0def90">XXH3&#95;mul128&#95;fold64</a>(uint64&#95;t lhs, uint64&#95;t rhs) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#if defined(&#95;&#95;SIZEOF&#95;INT128&#95;&#95;) ||                                              \\</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194"><Highlight kind="preprocessor">    (defined(&#95;INTEGRAL&#95;MAX&#95;BITS) &amp;&amp; &#95;INTEGRAL&#95;MAX&#95;BITS &gt;= 128)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t product = (&#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t)lhs &#42; (&#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t)rhs;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t(product) ^ uint64&#95;t(product &gt;&gt; 64);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; First calculate all of the cross products. &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t lo&#95;lo = (lhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF) &#42; (rhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t hi&#95;lo = (lhs &gt;&gt; 32) &#42; (rhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t lo&#95;hi = (lhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF) &#42; (rhs &gt;&gt; 32);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t hi&#95;hi = (lhs &gt;&gt; 32) &#42; (rhs &gt;&gt; 32);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; Now add the products together. These will never overflow. &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t cross = (lo&#95;lo &gt;&gt; 32) + (hi&#95;lo &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF) + lo&#95;hi;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="207"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t upper = (hi&#95;lo &gt;&gt; 32) + (cross &gt;&gt; 32) + hi&#95;hi;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t lower = (cross &lt;&lt; 32) | (lo&#95;lo &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> upper ^ lower;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#endif</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; If we reinterpret the 64x2 vectors as 32x4 vectors, we can use a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; de-interleave operation for 4 lanes in 1 step with &#96;vuzpq&#95;u32&#96; to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="392"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; get one vector with the low 32 bits of each lane, and one vector</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="393"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; with the high 32 bits of each lane.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="394"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="395"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; The intrinsic returns a double vector because the original ARMv7-a</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="399"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;  &#91; dk11L | dk11H | dk12L | dk12H &#93; -&gt; &#91; dk11L | dk12L | dk21L | dk22L &#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00565" /><CodeLine lineNumber="565"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; ==========================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00566" /><CodeLine lineNumber="566"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; XXH3 128 bits (a.k.a XXH128)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00567" /><CodeLine lineNumber="567"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; ==========================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00568" /><CodeLine lineNumber="568"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; XXH3&#39;s 128-bit variant has better mixing and strength than the 64-bit</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00569" /><CodeLine lineNumber="569"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; variant, even without counting the significantly larger output size.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="570"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="571"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; For example, extra steps are taken to avoid the seed-dependent collisions</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="572"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; in 17-240 byte inputs (See XXH3&#95;mix16B and XXH128&#95;mix32B).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="573"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="574"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; This strength naturally comes at the cost of some speed, especially on short</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="575"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; lengths. Note that longer hashes are about as fast as the 64-bit version</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="576"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; due to it using only a slight modification of the 64-bit loop.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="577"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; XXH128 is also more oriented towards 64-bit machines. It is still extremely</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; fast for a &#95;128-bit&#95; hash on 32-bit (it usually clears XXH64).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;!</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @internal</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @def XXH&#95;rotl32(x,r)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @brief 32-bit rotate left.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @param x The 32-bit integer to be rotated.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @param r The number of bits to rotate.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @pre</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;   @p r &gt; 0 &amp;&amp; @p r &lt; 32</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @note</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;   @p x and @p r may be evaluated multiple times.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @return The rotated result.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#if &#95;&#95;has&#95;builtin(&#95;&#95;builtin&#95;rotateleft32) &amp;&amp;                                   \\</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><Highlight kind="preprocessor">    &#95;&#95;has&#95;builtin(&#95;&#95;builtin&#95;rotateleft64)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl32 &#95;&#95;builtin&#95;rotateleft32</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl64 &#95;&#95;builtin&#95;rotateleft64</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; Note: although &#95;rotl exists for minGW (GCC under windows), performance seems</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; poor &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#elif defined(&#95;MSC&#95;VER)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl32(x, r) &#95;rotl(x, r)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl64(x, r) &#95;rotl64(x, r)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605" lineLink="#a70a4b202f9523a2a811da16cde3f52eb"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl32(x, r) (((x) &lt;&lt; (r)) | ((x) &gt;&gt; (32 - (r))))</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606" lineLink="#a056473e50ab5e7acb43d00ca3d41632e"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl64(x, r) (((x) &lt;&lt; (r)) | ((x) &gt;&gt; (64 - (r))))</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="607"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#endif</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="609" lineLink="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#define XXH&#95;mult32to64(x, y) ((uint64&#95;t)(uint32&#95;t)(x) &#42; (uint64&#95;t)(uint32&#95;t)(y))</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;!</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00612" /><CodeLine lineNumber="612"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @brief Calculates a 64-&gt;128-bit long multiply.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00613" /><CodeLine lineNumber="613"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00614" /><CodeLine lineNumber="614"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Uses &#96;&#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t&#96; and &#96;&#95;umul128&#96; if available, otherwise uses a scalar</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00615" /><CodeLine lineNumber="615"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; version.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00616" /><CodeLine lineNumber="616"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00617" /><CodeLine lineNumber="617"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @param lhs , rhs The 64-bit integers to be multiplied</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00618" /><CodeLine lineNumber="618"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @return The 128-bit result represented in an @ref XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00619" /><CodeLine lineNumber="619"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00620" /><CodeLine lineNumber="620" lineLink="#a5a010401dcddb43e0a6fdcac9564d69b"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> <a href="#a5a010401dcddb43e0a6fdcac9564d69b">XXH&#95;mult64to128</a>(uint64&#95;t lhs, uint64&#95;t rhs) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00621" /><CodeLine lineNumber="621"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00622" /><CodeLine lineNumber="622"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; GCC/Clang &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t method.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; On most 64-bit targets, GCC and Clang define a &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t type.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; This is usually the best way as it usually uses a native long 64-bit</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; multiply, such as MULQ on x86&#95;64 or MUL + UMULH on aarch64.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00627" /><CodeLine lineNumber="627"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; Usually.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; Despite being a 32-bit platform, Clang (and emscripten) define this type</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; despite not having the arithmetic for it. This results in a laggy</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; compiler builtin call which calculates a full 128-bit multiply.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; In that case it is best to use the portable one.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; https://github.com/Cyan4973/xxHash/issues/211#issuecomment-515575677</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#if (defined(&#95;&#95;GNUC&#95;&#95;) || defined(&#95;&#95;clang&#95;&#95;)) &amp;&amp; !defined(&#95;&#95;wasm&#95;&#95;) &amp;&amp;         \\</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><Highlight kind="preprocessor">        defined(&#95;&#95;SIZEOF&#95;INT128&#95;&#95;) ||                                          \\</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><Highlight kind="preprocessor">    (defined(&#95;INTEGRAL&#95;MAX&#95;BITS) &amp;&amp; &#95;INTEGRAL&#95;MAX&#95;BITS &gt;= 128)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00640" /><CodeLine lineNumber="640"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> product = (&#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t)lhs &#42; (&#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t)rhs;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00641" /><CodeLine lineNumber="641"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> r128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00642" /><CodeLine lineNumber="642"><Highlight kind="normal">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = (uint64&#95;t)(product);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00643" /><CodeLine lineNumber="643"><Highlight kind="normal">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = (uint64&#95;t)(product &gt;&gt; 64);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00644" /><CodeLine lineNumber="644"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> r128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00645" /><CodeLine lineNumber="645"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00646" /><CodeLine lineNumber="646"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00647" /><CodeLine lineNumber="647"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; MSVC for x64&#39;s &#95;umul128 method.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00648" /><CodeLine lineNumber="648"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00649" /><CodeLine lineNumber="649"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; uint64&#95;t &#95;umul128(uint64&#95;t Multiplier, uint64&#95;t Multiplicand, uint64&#95;t</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; &#42;HighProduct);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00651" /><CodeLine lineNumber="651"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00652" /><CodeLine lineNumber="652"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; This compiles to single operand MUL on x64.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00653" /><CodeLine lineNumber="653"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00654" /><CodeLine lineNumber="654"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#elif (defined(&#95;M&#95;X64) || defined(&#95;M&#95;IA64)) &amp;&amp; !defined(&#95;M&#95;ARM64EC)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00655" /><CodeLine lineNumber="655"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00656" /><CodeLine lineNumber="656"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#ifndef &#95;MSC&#95;VER</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#pragma intrinsic(&#95;umul128)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00658" /><CodeLine lineNumber="658"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#endif</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00659" /><CodeLine lineNumber="659"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t product&#95;high;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00660" /><CodeLine lineNumber="660"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> product&#95;low = &#95;umul128(lhs, rhs, &amp;product&#95;high);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00661" /><CodeLine lineNumber="661"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> r128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00662" /><CodeLine lineNumber="662"><Highlight kind="normal">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = product&#95;low;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00663" /><CodeLine lineNumber="663"><Highlight kind="normal">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = product&#95;high;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00664" /><CodeLine lineNumber="664"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> r128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00665" /><CodeLine lineNumber="665"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00666" /><CodeLine lineNumber="666"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00667" /><CodeLine lineNumber="667"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; MSVC for ARM64&#39;s &#95;&#95;umulh method.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00668" /><CodeLine lineNumber="668"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00669" /><CodeLine lineNumber="669"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; This compiles to the same MUL + UMULH as GCC/Clang&#39;s &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t method.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00670" /><CodeLine lineNumber="670"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00671" /><CodeLine lineNumber="671"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#elif defined(&#95;M&#95;ARM64) || defined(&#95;M&#95;ARM64EC)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00672" /><CodeLine lineNumber="672"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00673" /><CodeLine lineNumber="673"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#ifndef &#95;MSC&#95;VER</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00674" /><CodeLine lineNumber="674"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#pragma intrinsic(&#95;&#95;umulh)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00675" /><CodeLine lineNumber="675"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#endif</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="676"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> r128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="677"><Highlight kind="normal">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = lhs &#42; rhs;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="678"><Highlight kind="normal">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = &#95;&#95;umulh(lhs, rhs);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="679"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> r128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="680"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="681"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="682"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; Portable scalar method. Optimized for 32-bit and 64-bit ALUs.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; This is a fast and simple grade school multiply, which is shown below</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; with base 10 arithmetic instead of base 0x100000000.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;           9 3 // D2 lhs = 93</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;         x 7 5 // D2 rhs = 75</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="690"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     ----------</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;           1 5 // D2 lo&#95;lo = (93 % 10) &#42; (75 % 10) = 15</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;         4 5 | // D2 hi&#95;lo = (93 / 10) &#42; (75 % 10) = 45</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;         2 1 | // D2 lo&#95;hi = (93 % 10) &#42; (75 / 10) = 21</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     + 6 3 | | // D2 hi&#95;hi = (93 / 10) &#42; (75 / 10) = 63</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     ---------</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="696"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;         2 7 | // D2 cross = (15 / 10) + (45 % 10) + 21 = 27</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="697"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     + 6 7 | | // D2 upper = (27 / 10) + (45 / 10) + 63 = 67</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="698"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     ---------</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="699"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;       6 9 7 5 // D4 res = (27 &#42; 10) + (15 % 10) + (67 &#42; 100) = 6975</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="700"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00701" /><CodeLine lineNumber="701"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; The reasons for adding the products like this are:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00702" /><CodeLine lineNumber="702"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;  1 It avoids manual carry tracking. Just like how</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00703" /><CodeLine lineNumber="703"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     (9 &#42; 9) + 9 + 9 = 99, the same applies with this for UINT64&#95;MAX.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00704" /><CodeLine lineNumber="704"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     This avoids a lot of complexity.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00705" /><CodeLine lineNumber="705"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00706" /><CodeLine lineNumber="706"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;  2 It hints for, and on Clang, compiles to, the powerful UMAAL</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00707" /><CodeLine lineNumber="707"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     instruction available in ARM&#39;s Digital Signal Processing extension</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="708"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     in 32-bit ARMv6 and later, which is shown below:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;         void UMAAL(xxh&#95;u32 &#42;RdLo, xxh&#95;u32 &#42;RdHi, xxh&#95;u32 Rn, xxh&#95;u32 Rm)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;         &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;             uint64&#95;t product = (uint64&#95;t)&#42;RdLo &#42; (uint64&#95;t)&#42;RdHi + Rn + Rm;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;             &#42;RdLo = (xxh&#95;u32)(product &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;             &#42;RdHi = (xxh&#95;u32)(product &gt;&gt; 32);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;         &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     This instruction was designed for efficient long multiplication, and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     allows this to be calculated in only 4 instructions at speeds</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     comparable to some 64-bit ALUs.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00721" /><CodeLine lineNumber="721"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;  3 It isn&#39;t terrible on other platforms. Usually this will be a couple</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="722"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;     of 32-bit ADD/ADCs.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="725"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; First calculate all of the cross products. &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00726" /><CodeLine lineNumber="726"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> lo&#95;lo = <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>(lhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF, rhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="727"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> hi&#95;lo = <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>(lhs &gt;&gt; 32, rhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="728"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> lo&#95;hi = <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>(lhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF, rhs &gt;&gt; 32);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="729"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> hi&#95;hi = <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>(lhs &gt;&gt; 32, rhs &gt;&gt; 32);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="730"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00731" /><CodeLine lineNumber="731"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; Now add the products together. These will never overflow. &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="732"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> cross = (lo&#95;lo &gt;&gt; 32) + (hi&#95;lo &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF) + lo&#95;hi;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="733"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> upper = (hi&#95;lo &gt;&gt; 32) + (cross &gt;&gt; 32) + hi&#95;hi;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> lower = (cross &lt;&lt; 32) | (lo&#95;lo &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> r128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><Highlight kind="normal">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = lower;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><Highlight kind="normal">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = upper;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> r128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="preprocessor">#endif</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;! Seems to produce slightly better code on GCC for some reason. &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744" lineLink="#aace3bad147eeed78a2f1cab33d506d59"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/compiler-h/#a338bdf98e9e600f582b7bef274bc9388">LLVM&#95;ATTRIBUTE&#95;ALWAYS&#95;INLINE</a> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">constexpr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint64&#95;t <a href="#aace3bad147eeed78a2f1cab33d506d59">XXH&#95;xorshift64</a>(uint64&#95;t v64,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><Highlight kind="normal">                                                               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">int</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> shift) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> v64 ^ (v64 &gt;&gt; shift);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/compiler-h/#a338bdf98e9e600f582b7bef274bc9388">LLVM&#95;ATTRIBUTE&#95;ALWAYS&#95;INLINE</a> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750" lineLink="#a1f9fe4a69b646dae9518d991adc12a00"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="#a1f9fe4a69b646dae9518d991adc12a00">XXH3&#95;len&#95;1to3&#95;128b</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint8&#95;t &#42;input, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> len, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint8&#95;t &#42;secret,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><Highlight kind="normal">                   uint64&#95;t seed) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; A doubled version of 1to3&#95;64b with different constants. &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; len = 1: combinedl = &#123; input&#91;0&#93;, 0x01, input&#91;0&#93;, input&#91;0&#93; &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; len = 2: combinedl = &#123; input&#91;1&#93;, 0x02, input&#91;0&#93;, input&#91;1&#93; &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; len = 3: combinedl = &#123; input&#91;2&#93;, 0x03, input&#91;0&#93;, input&#91;1&#93; &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint8&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> c1 = input&#91;0&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint8&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> c2 = input&#91;len &gt;&gt; 1&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint8&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> c3 = input&#91;len - 1&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint32&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> combinedl = ((uint32&#95;t)c1 &lt;&lt; 16) | ((uint32&#95;t)c2 &lt;&lt; 24) |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><Highlight kind="normal">                             ((uint32&#95;t)c3 &lt;&lt; 0) | ((uint32&#95;t)len &lt;&lt; 8);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint32&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> combinedh = <a href="#a70a4b202f9523a2a811da16cde3f52eb">XXH&#95;rotl32</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a2a584ab307c8e962527df226089a7470">byteswap</a>(combinedl), 13);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> bitflipl =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><Highlight kind="normal">      (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#ae865d5defb8785b365f342375822beaa">endian::read32le</a>(secret) ^ <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#ae865d5defb8785b365f342375822beaa">endian::read32le</a>(secret + 4)) + seed;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> bitfliph =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"><Highlight kind="normal">      (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#ae865d5defb8785b365f342375822beaa">endian::read32le</a>(secret + 8) ^ <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#ae865d5defb8785b365f342375822beaa">endian::read32le</a>(secret + 12)) - seed;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> keyed&#95;lo = (uint64&#95;t)combinedl ^ bitflipl;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> keyed&#95;hi = (uint64&#95;t)combinedh ^ bitfliph;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> h128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"><Highlight kind="normal">  h128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = <a href="#acc6968c79b8da93dea87b708f2fe2734">XXH64&#95;avalanche</a>(keyed&#95;lo);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00772" /><CodeLine lineNumber="772"><Highlight kind="normal">  h128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = <a href="#acc6968c79b8da93dea87b708f2fe2734">XXH64&#95;avalanche</a>(keyed&#95;hi);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00773" /><CodeLine lineNumber="773"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> h128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00774" /><CodeLine lineNumber="774"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00775" /><CodeLine lineNumber="775"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/compiler-h/#a338bdf98e9e600f582b7bef274bc9388">LLVM&#95;ATTRIBUTE&#95;ALWAYS&#95;INLINE</a> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777" lineLink="#a611ba08ac061c11dce0a30072099ba3c"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="#a611ba08ac061c11dce0a30072099ba3c">XXH3&#95;len&#95;4to8&#95;128b</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint8&#95;t &#42;input, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> len, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint8&#95;t &#42;secret,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00778" /><CodeLine lineNumber="778"><Highlight kind="normal">                   uint64&#95;t seed) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00779" /><CodeLine lineNumber="779"><Highlight kind="normal">  seed ^= (uint64&#95;t)<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a2a584ab307c8e962527df226089a7470">byteswap</a>((uint32&#95;t)seed) &lt;&lt; 32;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00780" /><CodeLine lineNumber="780"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint32&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> input&#95;lo = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#ae865d5defb8785b365f342375822beaa">endian::read32le</a>(input);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00781" /><CodeLine lineNumber="781"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint32&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> input&#95;hi = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#ae865d5defb8785b365f342375822beaa">endian::read32le</a>(input + len - 4);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00782" /><CodeLine lineNumber="782"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> input&#95;64 = input&#95;lo + ((uint64&#95;t)input&#95;hi &lt;&lt; 32);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00783" /><CodeLine lineNumber="783"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> bitflip =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00784" /><CodeLine lineNumber="784"><Highlight kind="normal">      (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 16) ^ <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 24)) + seed;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00785" /><CodeLine lineNumber="785"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> keyed = input&#95;64 ^ bitflip;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00786" /><CodeLine lineNumber="786"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00787" /><CodeLine lineNumber="787"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; Shift len to the left to ensure it is even, this avoids even multiplies.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00788" /><CodeLine lineNumber="788"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00789" /><CodeLine lineNumber="789"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> m128 = <a href="#a5a010401dcddb43e0a6fdcac9564d69b">XXH&#95;mult64to128</a>(keyed, <a href="#a502e23a6442aeb2e9d55069d0f600e7e">PRIME64&#95;1</a> + (len &lt;&lt; 2));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00790" /><CodeLine lineNumber="790"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00791" /><CodeLine lineNumber="791"><Highlight kind="normal">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> += (m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> &lt;&lt; 1);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00792" /><CodeLine lineNumber="792"><Highlight kind="normal">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> ^= (m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> &gt;&gt; 3);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00793" /><CodeLine lineNumber="793"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00794" /><CodeLine lineNumber="794"><Highlight kind="normal">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = <a href="#aace3bad147eeed78a2f1cab33d506d59">XXH&#95;xorshift64</a>(m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a>, 35);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00795" /><CodeLine lineNumber="795"><Highlight kind="normal">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> &#42;= <a href="#af96c90d6eedd426a1e2213b4f9fbbc27">PRIME&#95;MX2</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00796" /><CodeLine lineNumber="796"><Highlight kind="normal">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = <a href="#aace3bad147eeed78a2f1cab33d506d59">XXH&#95;xorshift64</a>(m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a>, 28);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00797" /><CodeLine lineNumber="797"><Highlight kind="normal">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = <a href="#a5f41b833306622b3b79b209e3829bbb1">XXH3&#95;avalanche</a>(m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00798" /><CodeLine lineNumber="798"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> m128;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00799" /><CodeLine lineNumber="799"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00800" /><CodeLine lineNumber="800"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00801" /><CodeLine lineNumber="801"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/compiler-h/#a338bdf98e9e600f582b7bef274bc9388">LLVM&#95;ATTRIBUTE&#95;ALWAYS&#95;INLINE</a> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00802" /><CodeLine lineNumber="802" lineLink="#a68128490131d65e06f6066616f80ddf5"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="#a68128490131d65e06f6066616f80ddf5">XXH3&#95;len&#95;9to16&#95;128b</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint8&#95;t &#42;input, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> len, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> uint8&#95;t &#42;secret,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00803" /><CodeLine lineNumber="803"><Highlight kind="normal">                    uint64&#95;t seed) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00804" /><CodeLine lineNumber="804"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> bitflipl =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00805" /><CodeLine lineNumber="805"><Highlight kind="normal">      (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 32) ^ <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 40)) - seed;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00806" /><CodeLine lineNumber="806"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> bitfliph =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00807" /><CodeLine lineNumber="807"><Highlight kind="normal">      (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 48) ^ <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 56)) + seed;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00808" /><CodeLine lineNumber="808"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> input&#95;lo = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(input);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00809" /><CodeLine lineNumber="809"><Highlight kind="normal">  uint64&#95;t input&#95;hi = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(input + len - 8);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00810" /><CodeLine lineNumber="810"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> m128 =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00811" /><CodeLine lineNumber="811"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="#a5a010401dcddb43e0a6fdcac9564d69b">XXH&#95;mult64to128</a>(input&#95;lo ^ input&#95;hi ^ bitflipl, <a href="#a502e23a6442aeb2e9d55069d0f600e7e">PRIME64&#95;1</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00812" /><CodeLine lineNumber="812"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00813" /><CodeLine lineNumber="813"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; Put len in the middle of m128 to ensure that the length gets mixed to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00814" /><CodeLine lineNumber="814"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; both the low and high bits in the 128x64 multiply below.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00815" /><CodeLine lineNumber="815"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00816" /><CodeLine lineNumber="816"><Highlight kind="normal">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> += (uint64&#95;t)(len - 1) &lt;&lt; 54;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00817" /><CodeLine lineNumber="817"><Highlight kind="normal">  input&#95;hi ^= bitfliph;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00818" /><CodeLine lineNumber="818"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00819" /><CodeLine lineNumber="819"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; Add the high 32 bits of input&#95;hi to the high 32 bits of m128, then</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00820" /><CodeLine lineNumber="820"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; add the long product of the low 32 bits of input&#95;hi and PRIME32&#95;2 to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00821" /><CodeLine lineNumber="821"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; the high 64 bits of m128.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00822" /><CodeLine lineNumber="822"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00823" /><CodeLine lineNumber="823"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; The best approach to this operation is different on 32-bit and 64-bit.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00824" /><CodeLine lineNumber="824"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00825" /><CodeLine lineNumber="825"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">sizeof</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#42;) &lt; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">sizeof</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(uint64&#95;t)) &#123; </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; 32-bit &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00826" /><CodeLine lineNumber="826"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00827" /><CodeLine lineNumber="827"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; 32-bit optimized version, which is more readable.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00828" /><CodeLine lineNumber="828"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00829" /><CodeLine lineNumber="829"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; On 32-bit, it removes an ADC and delays a dependency between the two</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00830" /><CodeLine lineNumber="830"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; halves of m128.high64, but it generates an extra mask on 64-bit.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00831" /><CodeLine lineNumber="831"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00832" /><CodeLine lineNumber="832"><Highlight kind="normal">    m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> += (input&#95;hi &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF00000000ULL) +</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00833" /><CodeLine lineNumber="833"><Highlight kind="normal">                   <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>((uint32&#95;t)input&#95;hi, <a href="#a6db4d465a9f3c93ce1369c017071c9fb">PRIME32&#95;2</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00834" /><CodeLine lineNumber="834"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00835" /><CodeLine lineNumber="835"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00836" /><CodeLine lineNumber="836"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; 64-bit optimized (albeit more confusing) version.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00837" /><CodeLine lineNumber="837"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00838" /><CodeLine lineNumber="838"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; Uses some properties of addition and multiplication to remove the mask:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00839" /><CodeLine lineNumber="839"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="840"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; Let:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="841"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    a = input&#95;hi.lo = (input&#95;hi &amp; 0x00000000FFFFFFFF)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="842"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    b = input&#95;hi.hi = (input&#95;hi &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF00000000)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00843" /><CodeLine lineNumber="843"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    c = PRIME32&#95;2</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="844"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00845" /><CodeLine lineNumber="845"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    a + (b &#42; c)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00846" /><CodeLine lineNumber="846"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; Inverse Property: x + y - x == y</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00847" /><CodeLine lineNumber="847"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    a + (b &#42; (1 + c - 1))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00848" /><CodeLine lineNumber="848"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; Distributive Property: x &#42; (y + z) == (x &#42; y) + (x &#42; z)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00849" /><CodeLine lineNumber="849"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    a + (b &#42; 1) + (b &#42; (c - 1))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00850" /><CodeLine lineNumber="850"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; Identity Property: x &#42; 1 == x</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00851" /><CodeLine lineNumber="851"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    a + b + (b &#42; (c - 1))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00852" /><CodeLine lineNumber="852"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00853" /><CodeLine lineNumber="853"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; Substitute a, b, and c:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00854" /><CodeLine lineNumber="854"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    input&#95;hi.hi + input&#95;hi.lo + ((uint64&#95;t)input&#95;hi.lo &#42; (PRIME32&#95;2</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00855" /><CodeLine lineNumber="855"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; - 1))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00856" /><CodeLine lineNumber="856"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00857" /><CodeLine lineNumber="857"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42; Since input&#95;hi.hi + input&#95;hi.lo == input&#95;hi, we get this:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00858" /><CodeLine lineNumber="858"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;    input&#95;hi + ((uint64&#95;t)input&#95;hi.lo &#42; (PRIME32&#95;2 - 1))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00859" /><CodeLine lineNumber="859"><Highlight kind="comment">     &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="860"><Highlight kind="normal">    m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> += input&#95;hi + <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>((uint32&#95;t)input&#95;hi, <a href="#a6db4d465a9f3c93ce1369c017071c9fb">PRIME32&#95;2</a> - 1);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="861"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00862" /><CodeLine lineNumber="862"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42; m128 ^= XXH&#95;swap64(m128 &gt;&gt; 64); &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00863" /><CodeLine lineNumber="863"><Highlight kind="normal">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> ^= <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a2a584ab307c8e962527df226089a7470">byteswap</a>(m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00864" /><CodeLine lineNumber="864"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00943" /><CodeLine lineNumber="943"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> acc;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00944" /><CodeLine lineNumber="944"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> i;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00945" /><CodeLine lineNumber="945"><Highlight kind="normal">  acc.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = len &#42; <a href="#a502e23a6442aeb2e9d55069d0f600e7e">PRIME64&#95;1</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00946" /><CodeLine lineNumber="946"><Highlight kind="normal">  acc.high64 = 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00947" /><CodeLine lineNumber="947"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00948" /><CodeLine lineNumber="948"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;  We set as &#96;i&#96; as offset + 32 We do this so that unchanged</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00949" /><CodeLine lineNumber="949"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; &#96;len&#96; can be used as upper bound. This reaches a sweet spot</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00950" /><CodeLine lineNumber="950"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; where both x86 and aarch64 get simple agen and good codegen</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00954" /><CodeLine lineNumber="954"><Highlight kind="normal">    acc = <a href="#a2fa22ae762463bb383e63bd381952344">XXH128&#95;mix32B</a>(acc, input + i - 32, input + i - 16, secret + i - 32,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00955" /><CodeLine lineNumber="955"><Highlight kind="normal">                        seed);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00956" /><CodeLine lineNumber="956"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00957" /><CodeLine lineNumber="957"><Highlight kind="normal">  acc.low64 = <a href="#a5f41b833306622b3b79b209e3829bbb1">XXH3&#95;avalanche</a>(acc.low64);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00958" /><CodeLine lineNumber="958"><Highlight kind="normal">  acc.high64 = <a href="#a5f41b833306622b3b79b209e3829bbb1">XXH3&#95;avalanche</a>(acc.high64);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00959" /><CodeLine lineNumber="959"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00960" /><CodeLine lineNumber="960"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; NB: &#96;i &lt;= len&#96; will duplicate the last 32-bytes if</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00961" /><CodeLine lineNumber="961"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; len % 32 was zero. This is an unfortunate necessity to keep</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00962" /><CodeLine lineNumber="962"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42; the hash result stable.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00963" /><CodeLine lineNumber="963"><Highlight kind="comment">   &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00964" /><CodeLine lineNumber="964"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (i = 160; i &lt;= len; i += 32) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
